    "body": "### Problem\n\nfor `'` mark, nvim_buf_get_mark always returns the position based on curwin and curbuf, no matter which bufnr is given.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* `$ seq 10 > 10; seq 20 > 20`\r\n* `$ nvim --clean -u NONE`\r\n* `:e 10`, `10ggm'` # curbuf=1, curwin=1000\r\n* `:vs 20`, `20ggm'` # curbuf=2, curwin=1001\r\n* we are in buf#2 win=1001\r\n* `:lua =vim.api.nvim_buf_get_mark(1, \"'\")` # seeing '{20, 0}', which is supposed to be `{10, 0}`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nfor `'` mark, nvim_buf_get_mark honors the bufnr param, and maybe accept a winid param.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nnvim 0.10\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
