            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "well i feel the `'>` is another story, i see you are using a keymap defined like this:\r\n```\r\n      vim.keymap.set(\r\n        \"v\",\r\n        \"<leader>r\",\r\n        slimux.send_highlighted_text,\r\n        { desc = \"Send currently highlighted text to configured tmux pane\" }\r\n      )\r\n```\r\n\r\naccording to the doc of `col()` \r\n```\r\n\t\t    v       In Visual mode: the start of the Visual area (the\r\n\t\t\t    cursor is the end).  When not in Visual mode\r\n\t\t\t    returns the cursor position.  **Differs from |'<| in\r\n\t\t\t    that it's updated right away.**\r\n```\r\n\r\ni think you can try this: \r\n```\r\n vim.keymap.set(\r\n        \"v\",\r\n        \"<leader>r\",\r\n        \":lua require'slimux'.send_highlighted_text()<cr>\",\r\n      )\r\n```\r\n\r\nor let the upstream use vim.region()/getregionpos() instead, which i'm not too sure.",
